race.comment: Not many of these have upside but THIBLOS (3) is a progressive galloper who looks as though he will relish the ground here. Strode up to sit on speed at Mornington last time and ran right away for an effortless maiden win. Looks suited by the extra ground and can measure up again. TAVISTOCK DANCER (4) is a seasoned galloper with some good recent form. Won two on end before a close-up fifth two back then fifth again last time in richer company. Has good speed and will take catching. AMAWASHA (6) raced in a similar race last time and finished sixth, beaten fourth lengths. Boxed on fairly and among the chances on best. JENNI THE TANK (9) gave a sight over 4000m last time at Ararat and faded late to fourth. Back in trip and can give a sight again here.
